==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*εὐαγγέλιον / euaggelion / yoo-ang-ghel'-ee-on

===Noun===
'''εὐαγγέλιον'''

# [[gospel]]; good news
# a reward for good news
# runner, messenger

===Etymology===
*"good messenger", from [[εὐ-]] ([[eu-]]) and [[αγγέλιον]] ([[angelion]], [[aggelos]])

===Transliterations===
*euaggelion
*euaggelion
*euangelion
*evangelion
*eujaggevlion

===Related terms====
*[[evangelise]], [[evangelize]]
*[[εὐαγγελίζω]]

